    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="651"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d651">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.415 C35/45.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">French Ambassador</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">French Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: A delegation presided over by
                    Monsieur Hanotaux, member of the French Academy, former Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs, and composed of some twenty persons, will soon arrive in America to
                    offer to the Champlain Committee a bust by Rodin with which to ornament the
                    monument now building at Crown Point.</p>
                <p>This delegation, which comprises several members of the French Academy, two
                    Generals, a Senator, the President of the Academy of Fine Arts, several members
                    of the Institut, etc., will come to New York on board the S. S. <hi
                        rend="italic">La France</hi> arriving about the 26th instant.</p>
                <p>I should be very grateful to your excellency if you would request the competent
                    authorities to expedite the landing and examination <pb facs="0557" n="441"
                        xml:id="pg_441"/> of the baggage of the delegation as much as compatible
                    with the regulations.</p>
                <p>The stay of the delegation in the United States must be very brief, as they
                    expect to depart after about ten days.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.].</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jusserand</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
